nunder consideration is representative of the general population of field\ndwarfs. In addition, the unexplained excess of dwarf galaxies in LCDM could be\nas small as a factor of ~ 1.8, given the current uncertainties in the\nmeasurement of the galactic velocity function. Both of these caveats highlight\nthe importance of upcoming uniform surveys with HI interferometers for\nadvancing our understanding of the issue.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 27 Nov 2015 16:57:27 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 11 May 2016 14:07:58 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-06-15"}
